a’s bank-based finance sector, and illustrated the pressing need to develop a more robust and multi-faceted financial infrastructure across the region. Looking ahead, sustained economic development in Southeast Asia will be constrained unless the region can embrace new sources of capital. Authored by experts in their respective fields, the chapters of this book examine such issues as the region’s current debt burden, the region’s banking sector since the 1997–98 crisis, micro-financing efforts in the region, new opportunities in project financing, developing venture capital capabilities, reviving foreign direct investment inflows, creating bond markets, developing the region’s lacklustre equity markets, and the potential benefits of financial integration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aFinance. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Economic Development.2bisacsh1 aChaisrisawatsuk, Santi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConroy, John D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreeman, Nick J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreeman, Nick J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGooptu, Sudarshan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHew, Denis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJin, Ngiam Kee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, Giles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhalil, Khalili, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKharas, Homi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKohsaka, Akira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLamberte, Mario B., econtributor.4ctb